title: ASX to drop, US bond yields surge
summary: Australian shares are set to tumble more than 1 per cent amid broad selling in New York. US 10-year yield leaps above 1.5pc. $A sheds 1pc. VIX surges 37pc.
author: Timothy Moore

title: Dow Jones closes at record high, briefly tops 32,000
summary: Australian shares are set to recoup most of Wednesday’s losses as US stocks reset higher. The Dow rose 425 points, after shares in Boeing surged.
author: Timothy Moore

title: Dow, S&P 500 edge higher as Powell deflects inflation concern
summary: Australian shares are poised to open lower as investors wrestle with concerns about inflation. The Dow and S&P 500 end modestly positive after early drops.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to slip as commodities extend gains
summary: Australian shares are set to open lower as tech selling accelerated into the close in New York, dragging the Nasdaq sharply lower.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to slip, Wall St steady, $A surges
summary: Australian shares set to extend Friday’s losses to start the week. $A leap puts US79¢ on the radar. Reporting season peak ahead.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to drop, Wall St slides on labour market weakness
summary: Australian shares are poised to open lower, dragged down by selling in Europe and on Wall Street. $A and gold flat. Iron ore spikes higher.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to drop, US rally runs into inflation worries
summary: Australian shares are poised to open lower. Wall Street closed mixed. Oil higher, gold lower. Bitcoin tops $US52,500. Jobs data ahead.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to slip, Wall St resets records, bitcoin tops $US50,000
summary: Australian shares are set to edge lower as Wall Street’s benchmarks struggled to hold gains after resetting record highs. US 10-yr yield surges 10bps to 1.31pc.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to rise, European shares rally on copper, oil
summary: Australian shares are poised to open higher, bolstered by gains in Europe. Wall St is closed for Presidents Day.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to rise, Wall St extends record run
summary: Australian shares are poised to open higher, bolstered by further gains in New York. Key to local sentiment will be how investors interpret Victoria’s latest COVID-19 lockdown
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to slip, S&P 500 and Nasdaq reset closing highs
summary: Australian shares are poised to edge lower at the open. Both the S&P 500 and Nasdaq edged higher. Oil snaps its eight-day advance. Bitcoin leaps.
author: Timothy Moore

title: Dow edges up on Powell’s cautious optimism
summary: The Federal Reserve chairman struck a dovish tone, reinforcing that the central bank is in no rush to lift interest rates.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to rise, Nasdaq resets record high
summary: Australian shares are set to open higher. US stocks fluctuate with tech lifting Nasdaq to a fresh record. $A, gold, oil, iron ore: each higher.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to slip; Wall St, bitcoin, oil, iron ore rally
summary: Australian shares were poised to open lower. In contrast, US stocks reset record highs. Bitcoin leaps. Oil tops $US60 a barrel.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to edge up, Wall St bulls are back, $A leaps
summary: Australian shares are set to rise at the open, bolstered by renewed hopes in New York on earnings and more stimulus money. Oil extends rally. Gold rebounds.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to rise, S&P 500 resets its closing high
summary: Australian shares are set to open higher, catching a rally that lifted the S&P 500 and Nasdaq to record closes. $A slides below US76¢. Gold drops below $US1800/oz.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to fall, Wall St advances
summary: Australian shares are set to open lower as Wall Street advances on earnings, banks. Alphabet jumps. $A little changed.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to rise, Wall St rallies, oil leaps
summary: Australian shares are set to rally, as global investors flooded back into equities, helped by rising oil prices. Iron ore dropped. $A lower.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to rise on Wall St rebound, RBA decision awaited
summary: Australian shares are poised to open higher, bolstered by a tech rebound on Wall Street. The RBA holds a policy meeting. Reporting season heats up.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to fall as correction concerns rise
summary: Australian shares are poised to start the month lower amid a slew of data, RBA and global market worries. Has the Reddit army triggered a rethink?
author: Timothy Moore
